==English==

===Intransitive verb phrase===
'''fly out''' (''simple past'', '''flew out''')
# To travel rapidly to a destination, typically on an airplane
#: ''I'm going to '''fly out''' to see you.''
# To rapidly emerge
#: ''Pieces '''flew out''' in all directions.''
#{{baseball}} To become [[out]] by hitting a [[foul ball]] which is caught
#: ''Jones '''flew out''' to lead off the third.''

===Noun phrase===
'''foul out'''
#{{baseball}} An instance of flying out
#: ''A '''fly out''' was recorded on the scorecard.''